USA Overall

As of yesterday, there has been a total of 22,450,809 cases of COVID-19 in the USA. This is a change of 208,338 (0.94%) new cases since the day prior. The 7 day moving average is currently 2.45e+05 new cases which is a -4.75% change since the day prior and 15.16% change since the week prior. The immediate trend is heading upward. Based on the addition of yesterday’s data, yesterday was not an inflection point (days since last inflection point: 10 –> 2021-01-01).

7-day moving average of new cases in the US (2020-01-21 to 2021-01-10)

References

ICU stress definitions:

  • low: less than 10% of ICU Usage
  • moderate: 10-29% of ICU Usage
  • high: 30-59% of ICU Usage
  • extreme: greater than 60% of ICU Usage

Inpatient stress definitions:

  • low: less than 5% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
  • moderate: 5-9% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
  • high: 10-19% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
  • extreme: greater than 20% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
